# NextDestination — Travel Planning Super App

> **"Stop searching. Start journeying."**
> A unified platform that solves the "Tab Fatigue" problem by combining flight comparison, hotel price parity, car rentals, public transit routes, arrival card info, currency tips, and smart travel intelligence into one seamless experience.

## Background & Problem

Travelers today must juggle **10+ tabs** across Skyscanner, Agoda, Booking.com, Google Flights, Rome2Rio, and TripAdvisor just to plan a single trip. No existing platform lets you:

1. Compare **all airline prices** for the same route in one view
2. Compare the **exact same hotel** price across Agoda, Booking.com, Airbnb, Expedia, and direct booking side-by-side
3. See **car rental** options alongside flights and hotels
4. Check **arrival card** requirements, **currency**, and **accepted payment methods** for your destination
5. Browse **train/MRT/LRT routes** for getting around once you land
6. Get **contextual, date-specific travel tips** (visa, weather, festivals, exchange rates)

NextDestination solves all of them.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope — MVP with Mock Data**: This plan builds a **fully functional front-end MVP** using Next.js with rich mock data to showcase the complete UX vision. Real API integrations (Amadeus, Skyscanner, hotel APIs, car rental APIs) are planned for Phase 2. This lets you validate the concept and iterate on the UI before investing in expensive API subscriptions.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tech Stack — Next.js (Production Grade)**:
> - **Framework**: Next.js (App Router) — SSR, routing, API routes, production-ready
> - **Styling**: Vanilla CSS with CSS Modules — full control, no utility-class bloat
> - **Fonts**: Google Fonts via `next/font` (Inter + Outfit)
> - **Maps**: Leaflet.js (free, open-source) for transit route visualization
> - **Animations**: CSS transitions + Intersection Observer for scroll reveals

---

## Core Features (MVP)

### 1. 🔍 Unified Natural Language Search
- Single search bar: *"KL to Tokyo, 5 days, RM5000 budget"*
- Auto-detect: origin, destination, dates, budget, number of travelers

### 2. ✈️ Flight Comparison — All Airlines
- Compare **all carriers** for the same route (AirAsia, MAS, JAL, Korean Air, Scoot, etc.)
- Sort by: Price · Duration · Stops · Value Score (price ÷ quality)
- Show codeshare info and baggage allowance

### 3. 🏨 Hotel Price Parity — All Platforms
- Same hotel shown with prices from **every major platform**:

| Platform      | Price/Night | Total (5N) | Member Rate | Book → |
|--------------|-------------|------------|-------------|--------|
| **Direct**    | RM 275      | RM 1,375   | —           | →      |
| Agoda         | RM 280      | RM 1,400   | RM 265      | →      |
| Booking.com   | RM 295      | RM 1,475   | RM 280      | →      |
| Airbnb        | RM 310      | RM 1,550   | —           | →      |
| Expedia       | RM 305      | RM 1,525   | RM 290      | →      |
| Trip.com      | RM 288      | RM 1,440   | RM 270      | →      |

- Highlights cheapest with glow + "Save RM175" badge
- Includes Airbnb listings matched to the same area

### 4. 🚗 Car Rental Comparison
- Compare rental providers (Hertz, Avis, local companies)
- Show: vehicle type, daily rate, insurance included, pickup/dropoff locations
- Auto-suggest based on destination (e.g. "Bali — car rental recommended, no rail network")

### 5. 🛂 Arrival Card & Entry Requirements
- Digital arrival card requirements for each destination
- Visa status based on passport nationality (default: Malaysian)
- Health declaration / vaccination requirements
- Customs allowance (duty-free limits, prohibited items)

### 6. 💱 Currency & Payment Methods
- Live exchange rate display (MYR → destination currency)
- Accepted payment methods at destination:
  - 💳 Credit cards widely accepted? Visa/Mastercard/Amex?
  - 📱 E-wallets? (Alipay, WeChat Pay, PayPay, GrabPay)
  - 💵 Cash-heavy society? ATM availability?
  - 🏪 Contactless/tap-to-pay support?
- Recommended: "Bring cash" vs "Card is fine" summary

### 7. 🚇 Public Transit Routes — Train/MRT/LRT
- Interactive transit map for destination city
- Airport → City center route options (train, bus, taxi, Grab)
- Key MRT/LRT lines with station names
- Fare estimates and travel time
- Tourist pass recommendations (e.g. "Tokyo Subway 72-Hour Pass — ¥1,500")

### 8. 🎯 Smart Travel Tips
- Contextual to selected destination AND dates:
  - 🛂 Visa: "Malaysian passport: 90 days visa-free in Japan"
  - 🌧️ Weather: "Monsoon expected — pack rain gear"
  - 🎏 Events: "Golden Week overlap — expect 30% higher prices"
  - 💴 Exchange: "MYR→JPY at 3-month high — book now"
  - 🚫 Culture: "Tipping is not customary in Japan"
  - ⚡ Safety: "Petty theft common in tourist areas — use hotel safe"

